pageContext.claim: “We will have a vaccine so soon you won't even believe it. Although they are trying to do a little bit of a political hit. Let's -- let's delay it just a little bit. Do you notice that? Let's delay the vaccine just a little bit.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that the development of a vaccine was delayed for political reasons or because of the election. Ironically, the process went faster than expected because the U.S. caseload was so high.
